

### Ham & Pork Stock
### Sweet Home Cafe p200

* 5lb fresh pork bones
* 3 T vegetable oil
* 2 yellow onions, chopped
* 2 carrots, sliced
* 2 celery stalks
* 5 garlic cloves
* 8q cold water + 1c to deglaze
* 2 smoked ham hocks
* 3 thyme sprigs
* 3 bay leaves
* 2 T black peppercorns
* 1 t juniper berries

* preheat oven to 350
* put bones in roasting pan and toss with vegetable oil
* roast for 45m
* add onions, carrots, celery, garlic and roast for 20m; until bones and veg are golden brown

* transfer bones to large stockpot
* add 1C water to roasting pan, heat on stovetop for 5m
* remove pan from heat
* scrape brown bits from pan bottom with wooden spoon; add contents to stockpot
* pour in 8q water and bring to a simmer
* cook for 1h at a gentle, steady simmer, skimming from the surface
* do not allow stock to boil

* after simmering, add ham hocks, thyme, bay leaves, peppercorns, juniper berries;
* cook over low heat for 8 hours longer

* strain stock through fine-mesh sieve and cool immediately
* use within 4 days or freeze for up to 1 month